  "prompt": "What language was spoken in the period of Lord Rama?",
  "response": "The language spoken during the period of Lord Rama, according to ancient Indian texts, was likely forms of early Sanskrit or Prakrit. Lord Rama is a central figure in the Hindu epic Ramayana, which is traditionally composed in Sanskrit by the sage Valmiki. Sanskrit was the literary and liturgical language of ancient India and was used extensively in Hindu religious and philosophical texts. Prakrit, a group of Middle Indo-Aryan languages, might have been spoken by the common people during that era.",
